## Actions
- test.yaml trace-tests + nightly-tests: "Install ClickHouse binary" step
  (bin/get_clickhouse.sh → WEAVE_CLICKHOUSE_BINARY via GITHUB_ENV) after the
  pip install step; "Run nox (ClickHouse Local Trace Server)" step after the
  dockerized step, same marker selection plus --trace-server=clickhouse-local.
- Deliberately NO actions/cache: repo uses none today; a ~280MB tarball from
  packages.clickhouse.com CDN downloads in seconds on GH runners and cache
  restore wouldn't be clearly faster. Revisit if the install step is slow.
- Omitted WF_CLICKHOUSE_HOST from the new step env: the plugin sets
  WF_CLICKHOUSE_HOST/PORT inside the pytest process at configure time.
  (noxfile forwards a fixed env-var list; None values are tolerated — the
  trace_no_server job already runs without these vars.)
- Validated with actionlint + yaml.safe_load; only pre-existing info-level
  shellcheck nits remain (untouched lines).

